From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 02:42:26 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] core: Sync float brightness from int setting on first boot

On first boot or after a factory reset, SettingsProvider populates the database
with a default integer value for SCREEN_BRIGHTNESS, but fails to initialize
the new SCREEN_BRIGHTNESS_FLOAT setting.

This creates a desynchronization:
1. DisplayPowerController sees the missing float and falls back to the
   framework default (config_screenBrightnessSettingDefaultFloat), turning
   the physical screen brightness up to ~50%.
2. The Settings App UI (BrightnessLevelPreferenceController) sees the
   missing float and falls back to the minimum brightness, incorrectly
   displaying the brightness slider at 0%.

This commit patches BrightnessSynchronizer to perform an initial
synchronization when it starts observing. If the float value is missing
(Float.NaN), it populates it directly from the existing integer setting,
ensuring the Settings App UI accurately reflects the physical hardware
brightness on first boot.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Change-Id: I2a52f611d3d27389e92dde92b08e6b4c9f54d1c1
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 core/java/com/android/internal/BrightnessSynchronizer.java | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/core/java/com/android/internal/BrightnessSynchronizer.java b/core/java/com/android/internal/BrightnessSynchronizer.java
index 8ff3c497662..7f256dea967 100644
--- a/core/java/com/android/internal/BrightnessSynchronizer.java
+++ b/core/java/com/android/internal/BrightnessSynchronizer.java
@@ -274,6 +274,11 @@ public class BrightnessSynchronizer{
             cr.unregisterContentObserver(this);
             cr.registerContentObserver(BRIGHTNESS_URI, false, this, UserHandle.USER_ALL);
             cr.registerContentObserver(BRIGHTNESS_FLOAT_URI, false, this, UserHandle.USER_ALL);
+
+            if (Float.isNaN(getScreenBrightnessFloat(mContext))) {
+                int currentBrightness = getScreenBrightnessInt(mContext);
+                mHandler.obtainMessage(MSG_UPDATE_FLOAT, currentBrightness, 0).sendToTarget();
+            }
         }
 
         public void stopObserving() {
